The proof leverages the measurability of the norm and the logarithm of the norm of the difference `f x - g y`, and uses the fact that the logarithm is well-defined (i.e., the norm is positive) almost everywhere. 

By verifying the `AESTronglyMeasurable` condition in both variables, we complete the proof of integrability for the product measure. 

